y features from version `2.35`; avoid deprecated APIs.\\n- Additional test dependencies only if necessary.\\n- All top-level test classes must be `public`.\\n- Do not compile/run tests manually; external workflow runs them.\\n- Tests should execute under Native Image by default.\\n- Each test must complete in under 60 seconds; use bounded waits/timeouts and close resources.\\n- Do not skip Native Image execution with assumptions/guards.\\n- Only catch `Error` with `NativeImageSupport.isUnsupportedFeatureError(e)` for true post-build dynamic class loading cases.\\n\\n## Progress\\n### Done\\n- [x] Replaced placeholder test at `tests/src/org.glassfish.jersey.media/jersey-media-json-jackson/2.35/src/test/java/org_glassfish_jersey_media/jersey_media_json_jackson/Jersey_media_json_jacksonTest.java`.\\n- [x] Made top-level test class `public`.\\n- [x] Added integration tests covering:\\n  - Explicit `JacksonFeature` registration.\\n  - Deserialization of generic JSON collections via `GenericType<List<Person>>`.\\n  - Serialization of JSON request entities.\\n  - Custom `ObjectMapper` via `ContextResolver<ObjectMapper>`.\\n  - JAXB annotation element-name handling.\\n  - Jersey auto-discovery of `JacksonFeature`.\\n- [x] Added local JDK `HttpServer` helper with daemon executor and cleanup.\\n- [x] Added Jersey client timeouts via `ClientProperties.CONNECT_TIMEOUT` and `ClientProperties.READ_TIMEOUT`.\\n- [x] Added necessary dependencies in `tests/src/org.glassfish.jersey.media/jersey-media-json-jackson/2.35/build.gradle`:\\n  - `org.glassfish.jersey.core:jersey-client:$libraryVersion`\\n  - `org.glassfish.jersey.inject:jersey-hk2:$libraryVersion`\\n- [x] Fixed compile error where `javax.ws.rs.client.Client` was used in try-with-resources; Jersey 2.35 `Client` has `close()` but is not `AutoCloseable`. Now uses explicit `try/finally { client.close(); }`.\\n- [x] Added native-image temp-dir runtime/build args in `build.gradle` after native compilation failed due to full system temp filesystem:\\n  - `-Djava.io.tmpdir=${nativeImageTempDir.absolutePath}`\\n  - `-H:TempDirectory=${nativeImageTempDir.absolutePath}`\\n  - `-J-Djava.io.tmpdir=${nativeImageTempDir.absolutePath}`\\n  - `TMPDIR`, `TMP`, `TEMP` via `addEnvVar(...)`.\\n\\n### In Progress\\n- [ ] Resolve/confirm remaining `nativeTestCompile` failure.\\n\\n### Blocked\\n- Native Image build fails before executing tests with:\\n  - `Fatal error: Unable to create temp directory for prefix driverRoot-: java.nio.file.FileSystemException: No space left on device`\\n- This persisted even after passing temp-dir overrides in `build.gradle`.\\n- JVM compile/test phase reached successfully after fixing `Client` cleanup; failure is during `:nativeTestCompile`.\\n\\n## Key Decisions\\n- **Use Jersey client + local JDK `HttpServer`**: Exercises the public Jersey/Jackson integration path without requiring a full Jersey server container dependency.\\n- **Register `JacksonFeature` explicitly in most tests**: Directly validates the public API feature.\\n- **Keep one auto-discovery test**: Covers `jersey-media-json-jackson` service auto-discovery behavior without duplicating explicit registration tests.\\n- **Use explicit `client.close()`**: Required because Jersey 2.35 `javax.ws.rs.client.Client` is not `AutoCloseable`.\\n- **Add `jersey-client` and `jersey-hk2` dependencies**: Needed to instantiate and use Jersey `ClientBuilder` with Jersey runtime injection.\\n- **Add native-image temp overrides**: Attempted workaround for environment’s full default temp filesystem.\\n\\n## Next Steps\\n1. Decide whether to keep or remove the temp-dir workaround in `build.gradle`; it was added for the environment issue but did not resolve the failure.\\n2. If continuing to debug native-image temp handling, inspect whether `BuildNativeImageTask.addEnvVar(...)` is actually applied to the native-image process and whether this GraalVM driver honors `-Djava.io.tmpdir`, `-H:TempDirectory`, or env vars before creating `driverRoot-*`.\\n3. If the environment remains full, report that the current failure is infrastructure-related and not caused by test code.\\n4. If Native Image progresses past compilation later, handle any real reachability/test failures from the new Jersey/Jackson tests.\\n\\n## Critical Context\\n- Main test file:\\n  - `tests/src/org.glassfish.jersey.media/jersey-media-json-jackson/2.35/src/test/java/org_glassfish_jersey_media/jersey_media_json_jackson/Jersey_media_json_jacksonTest.java`\\n- Build file:\\n  - `tests/src/org.glassfish.jersey.media/jersey-media-json-jackson/2.35/build.gradle`\\n- Current test methods:\\n  - `registeredJacksonFeatureReadsGenericJsonCollections`\\n  - `registeredJacksonFeatureWritesJsonRequestEntities`\\n  - `contextResolverCustomizesJacksonObjectMapper`\\n  - `jacksonJaxbProviderHonorsJaxbElementNames`\\n  - `jacksonFeatureIsAutoDiscoveredByJerseyClient`\\n- Important helper methods/classes:\\n  - `newJacksonClient(Object... providers)`\\n  - `newBaseClient()`\\n  - `newClientConfig()`\\n  - `sendJson(HttpExchange exchange, int status, String json)`\\n  - `TestServer`\\n  - `DaemonThreadFactory`\\n  - DTO/provider nested classes: `Person`, `Order`, `Acknowledgement`, `NamingBean`, `JaxbNamedEntity`, `SnakeCaseObjectMapperResolver`\\n- First compile failure fixed:\\n  - `Client cannot be converted to AutoCloseable`\\n- Current native-image failure:\\n  - `Fatal error: Unable to create temp directory for prefix driverRoot-: java.nio.file.FileSystemException: No space left on device`\\n- Native-image command line includes the added args, but failure still occurs:\\n  - `-H:TempDirectory=.../build/tmp/native-image`\\n  - `-J-Djava.io.tmpdir=.../build/tmp/native-image`\\n  - later also `-Djava.io.tmpdir=.../build/tmp/native-image`\\n\\n<read-files>\\ntests/src/org.example/library/0.0.1/build.gradle\\ntests/src/org.glassfish.jersey.media/jersey-media-json-jackson/2.35/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json\\ntests/tck-b